19 (b) The personal curriculum must do all of the following:
20 (i) Incorporate as much of the subject area content
21 expectations of the Michigan merit standard required under
22 subsection (1) and section 1278a(1)(a) as is practicable for the
23 pupil.
24 (ii) Establish measurable goals that the pupil must achieve
25 while enrolled in high school.
26 (iii) Provide a method to evaluate whether the pupil achieved
27 the goals described in subparagraph (ii).
28 (iv) Align with the pupil's educational development plan
29 developed under subsection (11).
CRM H00055'25 (H-3) i0e4q7

21
1 (c) Before it takes effect, the personal curriculum must be
2 agreed to by the pupil's parent or legal guardian and by the
3 superintendent of the school district or chief executive of the
4 public school academy or his or her designee.
5 (d) The pupil's parent or legal guardian shall communicate
6 with each of the pupil's teachers to monitor the pupil's progress
7 toward the goals contained in the pupil's personal curriculum.
8 (e) Revisions may be made in the personal curriculum if the
9 revisions are developed and agreed to in the same manner as the
10 original personal curriculum.
11 (f) The English language arts credit requirements of
12 subsection (1)(a) and the science credit requirements of subsection
13 (1)(b) are not subject to modification as part of a personal
14 curriculum under this subsection.
15 (g) The mathematics credit requirements of section
16 1278a(1)(a)(i) may be modified as part of a personal curriculum if
17 the pupil successfully completes at least 3-1/2 3 total credits of
18 the mathematics credits required under that section before
19 completing high school, including algebra I and geometry, and
20 successfully completes at least 1 mathematics credit during his or
21 her the pupil's final 2 years of high school. The algebra II credit
22 required under that section may be modified as part of a personal
23 curriculum under this subsection if the pupil meets 1 or more of
24 the following:
25 (i) Successfully completes the same content as 1 semester of
26 algebra II, as determined by the department.
27 (ii) Elects to complete the same content as algebra II over 2
28 years, with a credit awarded for each of those 2 years, and
29 successfully completes that content.
CRM H00055'25 (H-3) i0e4q7

22
1 (iii) Enrolls in a formal career and technical education program
2 or curriculum and in that program or curriculum successfully
3 completes the same content as the algebra II benchmarks assessed on
4 the department-prescribed state high school assessment, as
5 determined by the department.
6 (iv) Successfully completes 1 semester of statistics, functions
7 and data analysis, or technical mathematics.
8 (h) The social science credit requirements of section
9 1278a(1)(a)(ii) may be modified as part of a personal curriculum
10 only if all of the following are met:
11 (i) The pupil has successfully completed 2 credits of the
12 social science credits required under section 1278a(1), including
13 the civics course described in section 1166(2).
14 (ii) The modification requires the pupil to complete 1
15 additional credit in English language arts, mathematics, or science
16 or 1 additional credit in a language other than English, or
17 requires the pupil to complete a formal career and technical
18 education program. This additional credit must be in addition to
19 the number of those credits otherwise required under subsection (1)
20 and section 1278a(1) or under section 1278a(2).
21 (i) The health and physical education credit requirement under
22 section 1278a(1)(a)(iii) may be modified as part of a personal
23 curriculum only if the modification requires the pupil to complete
24 1 additional credit in English language arts, mathematics, or
25 science or 1 additional credit in a language other than English, or
26 requires the pupil to complete a formal career and technical
27 education program. This additional credit must be in addition to
28 the number of those credits otherwise required under subsection (1)
29 and section 1278a(1) or under section 1278a(2).
