18 modification is consistent with both the pupil's educational
19 development plan under subsection (11) and the pupil's
20 individualized education program. If the superintendent of public
21 instruction has reason to believe that a school district or a
22 public school academy is allowing modifications inconsistent with
23 the requirements of this subdivision, the superintendent of public
24 instruction shall monitor the school district or public school
