1 (l) If a pupil transfers to a school district or public school
2 academy from out of state or from a nonpublic school, the pupil's
3 parent or legal guardian may request, as part of the pupil's
4 personal curriculum, a modification of the Michigan merit standard
5 requirements that would not otherwise be allowed under this
6 section. The school district or public school academy may allow
7 this additional modification for a transfer pupil if all of the
8 following are met:
9 (i) The transfer pupil has successfully completed at least the
10 equivalent of 2 years of high school credit out of state or at a
11 nonpublic school. The school district or public school academy may
12 use appropriate assessment examinations to determine what credits,
13 if any, the pupil has earned out of state or at a nonpublic school
14 that may be used to satisfy the curricular requirements of the
15 Michigan merit standard and this subdivision.
16 (ii) The transfer pupil's personal curriculum incorporates as
17 much of the subject area content expectations of the Michigan merit
18 standard as is practicable for the pupil.
19 (iii) The transfer pupil's personal curriculum requires the
20 pupil to successfully complete at least 1 mathematics course during
21 his or her the transfer pupil's final year of high school
22 enrollment. In addition, if the transfer pupil is enrolled in the
23 school district or public school academy for at least 1 full school
24 year, both of the following apply:
25 (A) The transfer pupil's personal curriculum must require that
26 this mathematics course is at least algebra I.
27 (B) If the transfer pupil demonstrates that he or she the
28 transfer pupil has mastered the content of algebra I, the transfer
29 pupil's personal curriculum must require that this mathematics
