11 social science credit requirement under section 1278a(1)(a)(ii).
12 (o) The department or a school district or public school
13 academy shall not limit or discourage the number of pupils with a
14 personal curriculum on any basis other than the best interests of
15 each individual pupil.
16 (p) A school district or public school academy annually shall
17 notify each of its pupils and a parent or legal guardian of each of
18 its pupils that all pupils are entitled to a personal curriculum
19 under this subsection. The annual notice must include an
20 explanation of what a personal curriculum is and state that if a
21 personal curriculum is requested, the public school or public
22 school academy will grant that request. The school district or
23 public school academy shall provide this annual notice to parents
24 and legal guardians by sending a written notice to each pupil's
25 home or by including the notice in a newsletter, student handbook,
26 or similar communication that is sent to a pupil's home, and also
27 shall post the notice on the school district's or public school
28 academy's website.
